While opposition parties continued with their calls for President Jacob Zuma to step down, the president on Wednesday took part in birthday celebrations at the Walter Sisulu square in Soweto. The celebration rally was put together by the African National Congress and saw supporters come out in their numbers to celebrate the day with Zuma, who turned 75. READ MORE: Cosatu wishes Zuma well on his birthday but won&#8217;t attend his party For more news your way, follow The Citizen on Facebook and Twitter.